--------------------------
I'll go further. I believe value investing is about going where you see the
value. If you determine CEG is a value buy for you, then so be it. You have to
know yourself too though. There is just something about a sharp, young guy
getting started with value investing and going into a utility stock and holding
it patiently until an idea of fair/full value is reached. (Why not though?) I
guess I don't fit that personality (or age or brains). If we're talking a
trade, or something short-term, not an investment, then I could see it easier.

If I were a student, maybe could scrape up say a few thousand to invest, I'd
look to where I could make use of my understanding of value investing, where
that would be an advantage, and where I could get good reward for the risk I
take. One idea might be to look also at some of these .50-$4.00 Chinese stocks
that are mentioned around SI (grispin here, for example). Once I started
looking, I found so many of these type stocks, it's almost overwhelming. I find
the analysis isn't so difficult (if we're talking p/bk, p/e, roe, debt/equity).
Finding the company and getting to the quarterly/annual reports is
time-consuming, and selecting buys from among the possibilities is a challenge.
I like packages, I'd go with a package of 5-8 such stocks. Of course, this is
sector investing, so is subject to risks in investing in China. It seems like
there is still the possibility of making 2,3 or more times one's investment
though if a carefully or luckily chosen stock is selected. One or two of those
in the package of 5-8 would really make a difference.

Anyway, I hold a bunch of dinky Chinese stocks and I'm going through a list of
more now to see if I find any that I might bet on...er...invest in.

So I remembered Dr. Ipsofacto, and that perhaps this sector might be something
that might appeal to you also.

Others here may have contrary or better ideas. Also, I want to be
opportunistic, so it's possible if circumstances change tomorrow, so will my
idea(s). And I've been wrong many, many times.
