From:geoffrey Wren
Re: GAM

Their expenses are a little higher than ADX. I checked GAM's 2009 annual
statement and they show the following for expenses:

Ratio of expenses to average net assets
applicable to Common Stock
1.93% 0.87% 1.11% 1.06% 1.25% [five years]

If one is looking at an alternative of an actively managed mutual fund, then
GAM looks pretty good, because that is about typical of actively managed mutual
funds, and there is the discount as an extra. For someone with a small stake,
GAM could be okay. Still I'd tend to prefer ADX because their expenses are
lower.

But I manage my own holdings for around .1%, and so see discounted CEF's from a
different angle.

I did notice GAM-B, a preferred, very safe, pays 6%, which might be of interest
to conservative investors.
