Date:3/14/2010 11:31:03 AM
From:Madharry
OT I thought you guys might find the following thought provoking and
interesting: This pertains to the Visteon's bankruptcy filing which I didnt
really follow and the author's comments that banruptcy proposals are structured
to provide the biggest benefit to management as opposed to any other specific
class of security holders. In this particular case. management which prior to
the bankruptcy held less than 1% of the equity will now end up with 10% of the
equity in the new company, while existing shareholders get wiped out.

http://www.distressed-debt-investing.com/2010/03/distressed-debt-equity-example
visteon.html
%EOM----------------------

