Date:3/14/2010 1:04:45 PM
From:Grantcw
Yes, if you can manage your portfolio for .1% fees, then cef's aren't for you.
I wish I could do that! :)

That being said, for general stock cef's with low admin fees selling at a
discount, I've monitored TY, ADX, and CET for a few years and like all 3. I've
only owned shares in CET.

In general, I think the higher the market we're at (think Dow 14k), the harder
it is for me find value stocks. At those points, cef's like this make more
sense to me as at least a temporary place to put investing dollars.

Right now, I still think we're at a place where individual value stocks are out
there in decent #'s and so I have less in cef's than I used to have, but as we
go up (hopefully), I will rotate more into these.

Interesting cef discussion...

