--
Aside: Have an HD unit in another car, and that's pretty good too. Better FM
and AM reception than regular radio, no fade under bridges (Sirius fades), no
monthly/yearly fee, and of course, the stations broadcasting in HD can and do
send info through the unit's screen (station id/song title/artist/ads). Perhaps
HD may becomee the main competitor to Sirius for content transmitted over the
airwaves.
